08\n| Viewers         = 3.48<ref name=\"1.08\">{{cite web|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-survivor-on-cbs-rises-to-two-year-high-in-total-viewers-chicago-med-and-chicago-fire-on-nbc-each-hit-four-year-best-audience-figures/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''Survivor'' on CBS Rises to Two-Year High in Total Viewers; ''Chicago Med'' and ''Chicago Fire'' on NBC Each Hit Four-Year Best Audience Figures|date=March 26, 2020|work=Programming Insider|access-date=April 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404144326/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-survivor-on-cbs-rises-to-two-year-high-in-total-viewers-chicago-med-and-chicago-fire-on-nbc-each-hit-four-year-best-audience-figures/|archive-date=April 4, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Teams choose two minifigures that are later determined to be heroes or villains. They then build their heroes'/villains' lairs and are put with another team to create a battle between their characters. Guest starring [[Terry Crews]].\n| LineColor       = FEEB39\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| Title           = Star Wars\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|8}}\n| ProdCode        = LEG-109\n| Viewers         = 3.64<ref name=\"1.09\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-8-2020.html|title=Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.8.2020|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|author-link=Mitch Metcalf|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = In the first challenge, teams were tasked to build a Lego structure that represented a [[Droid (Star Wars)|droid]] that fit into the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe with some form of motorized action. In the second challenge, teams had to reconstruct one of three iconic scenes from the ''Star Wars'' films: the attack on ice planet [[Hoth]] from ''[[The Empire Strikes Back]]'', the fight on the forest moon of [[Endor (Star Wars)|Endor]] in ''[[Return of the Jedi]]'', and defending the base on Crait in ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi|The Last Jedi]]''. Teams selected their scenes based on their rankings from the first challenge. Featured appearances of [[C-3PO]], [[R2-D2]], and [[BB-8]]\n| LineColor       = FEEB39\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| Title           = Finals\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n| ProdCode        = LEG-110\n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FEEB39\n}}\n}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe series is jointly produced by [[Endemol Shine North America]], UK-based independent production company Tuesday's Child, and [[Plan B Entertainment]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/lego-masters-u-s-version-of-hit-uk-series-in-works-by-endemol-shine-north-america-tuesdays-child-plan-b-1202532023/|title='Lego Masters': U.S. Version Of Hit UK Series In Works By Endemol Shine North America, Tuesday's Child & Plan B|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=2019-01-09|website=Deadline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n\nCasting for the series was announced at [[San Diego Comic-Con|San Diego Comic Con 2019]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebrickfan.com/lego-masters-us-now-casting-for-contestants/|title=LEGO Masters US Now Casting for Contestants|last=Tran|first=Allen \"Tormentalous\"|date=2019-07-20|website=The Brick Fan|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref> and was described on the casting website as seeking \"the most creative, passionate, and innovative Lego builder teams of 2.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.legomasters.tv/|title=LEGO Masters|last=|first=|date=|website=legomasters.tv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref> The casting website stated that filming was to take place over seven weeks between October and December 2019.\n\nAccording to Corbett, there were more than three million Lego bricks available for teams to use during the challenges.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://decider.com/2020/02/26/lego-masters-amy-corbett-brickmaster-interview/|title=''Lego Masters'' on Fox: Brickmaster Amy Corbett Is Helping Build a Family-Friendly Hit|first=Brett|last=White|date=February 26, 2020|access-date=February 28, 2020|work=[[Decider (website)|Decider]]}}</ref> Lego artist [[Nathan Sawaya]] served as a consulting producer for the show, helping to design some of the example pieces, the challenges, and the show's Lego-based trophy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.avclub.com/lego-masters-nathan-sawaya-on-a-life-devoted-to-playing-1841434844|title=Lego Masters' Nathan Sawaya on a life devoted to playing with Lego|first=Marah|last=Eakin|date=February 4, 2020|access-date=February 4, 2020|work=[[The A.V. Club]]}}</ref>\n\n== Ratings ==\n{{Television episode ratings\n| refs_col   = y\n\n| title1     = Dream Park Theme Park\n| date1      = {{nowrap|February 5, 2020}}\n| rs1        = 1.6/7\n| viewers1   = 4.73\n| dvr1       = 1.0\n| dvrv1      = 2.90\n| total1     = 2.6\n| totalv1    = 7.64\n| ref1       = <ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n\n| title2     = Space Smash\n| date2      = {{nowrap|February 12, 2020}}\n| rs2        = 1.2/6\n| viewers2   = 3.50\n| dvr2       = 0.8\n| dvrv2      = 2.24\n| total2     = 1.9\n| totalv2    = 5.74\n| ref2       = <ref name=\"1.02\"/>\n\n| title3     = Cut in Half\n| date3      = {{nowrap|February 19, 2020}}\n| rs3        = 1.0/5\n| viewers3   = 2.98\n| dvr3       = 0.8\n| dvrv3      = 2.13\n| total3     = 1.7\n| totalv3    = 5.11\n| ref3       = <ref name=\"1.03\"/>\n\n| title4     = Movie Genres\n| date4      = {{nowrap|February 26, 2020}}\n| rs4        = 1.0/5\n| viewers4   = 3.03\n| dvr4       = 0.7\n| dvrv4      = 1.89\n| total4     = 1.7\n| totalv4    = 4.92\n| ref4       = <ref name=\"1.04\"/>\n\n| title5     = Mega City Block\n| date5      = {{nowrap|March 4, 2020}}\n| rs5        = 0.9/5\n| viewers5   = 2.90\n| dvr5       = 0.7\n| dvrv5    