 in Half\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|19}}\n| ProdCode        = LEG-103\n| Viewers         = 2.98<ref name=\"1.03\">{{cite web|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-record-high-democratic-debate-viewership-with-debut-of-michael-bloomberg-on-presidential-candidates-debate-stage/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: Record-High Democratic Debate Viewership with Debut of Michael Bloomberg on Presidential Candidates Debate Stage|work=Programming Insider|date=February 21, 2020|access-date=February 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307191337/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-record-high-democratic-debate-viewership-with-debut-of-michael-bloomberg-on-presidential-candidates-debate-stage/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Teams select one of several household objects that have been sawed in half, and must build a Lego structure extending from it that creatively builds out the missing half while integrating a story with the object.\n| LineColor       = FEEB39\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = Movie Genres\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|26}}\n| ProdCode        = LEG-104\n| Viewers         = 3.03<ref name=\"1.04\">{{cite web|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-real-housewives-of-new-jersey-on-bravo-rises-to-season-highs-in-total-viewers-and-adults-18-49-with-tenth-season-finale/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''Real Housewives of New Jersey'' on Bravo Rises to Season-Highs in Total Viewers and Adults 18-49 with Tenth Season Finale|work=Programming Insider|date=February 28, 2020|access-date=March 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307191454/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-real-housewives-of-new-jersey-on-bravo-rises-to-season-highs-in-total-viewers-and-adults-18-49-with-tenth-season-finale/|archive-date=March 7, 2020|url-s